	   <tr><td colspan=2>This post add a little different with those post above where no fraction hit take in consider :)<br><br>From lvl 1-5<br>I start in gfay as high elf killing bat.wasp and orc prawn.<br><br>From lvl 5-11 12<br>I headed orc hill and cb to get lvl<br><br>From lvl 12-16<br>I went to LF to kill sister(great exp esp woth the neck quest<br><br>From lvl 16-20<br>I stay in EK killing hound and crag great exp but poor loot<br><br>From lvl 21-25<br>I headed to SK killing bird and paw(almost fully camp everytime :)<br><br>From lvl 25 to 29<br>I went back to LF killing Saben great exp with great loot :)<br><br>From 29-35<br>I went to various place to kill druid range from EK druid ring to WC EC druid ring<br><br>From lvl 35-39<br>I headed back to Sk camping bard<br><br>From lvl 39 40-48<br>I start camping gnome guard(halv) great exp and loot :)<br><br>From 48 onwards<br>Start to get a group at lguk or solb where u lvl till 49 and u r on your own to solo IG in everfrost where u can outlvl very fast to 45<br><br>All the above memtion are mainly for soloing only once a while get a group. The exp gain are fairly decent ranging from 1/2 half hrs per bubb to 2 hrs per bubb (except hell lvl 35 40 45 abt 4 hrs per bubb) so basically u could lvl fast at a constant logging time at 4-6 hrs per day and u could almost get 2-3 lvl per week or more :)And the spawn rate pet mob is abt 6min each not worth if waiting to long :)<br><br>But the fraction hit are very serious as you cannot go to place like qeynos kelethin freeport etc but who cares :) exp is more important :)<br><br>Once u get lvl to 49 u r almost strong enough to do fraction lvling first headed to MM where u can start camping NS 5int wis meanwhile getting fraction for Bard then to BB(blackburrow) since u r going everfrost to gain fraction with qeynos guard and of course the steel warrior fraction which works in North freeport :) and oso allow u to do the hero bracer quest :)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
