	   <a name=9667139196182></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9667139196182><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=9667139196182>My Leveling Experiences.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=9667139196182#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=684><span id=Sage>Eendyar</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>16 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 19th 3:38 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This guide has 3 parts so feel free to skip through them&nbsp;&nbsp;<br>                                                                                          <br>part 1 - General Leveling and exp places                          <br>part 2 - Research info                                                        <br>part 3 - Extra mage info (This is good stuff, dont miss it)  <br>**********************************************<br><br>-----------------------------------------------<br>General Leveling and exp possibilites<br>-----------------------------------------------<br><br>A mage is a very interesting class.  Balanced for soloing yet a very powerful add on for groups.  A caster and a tank in 1, a mage with his trusty pet can tip the balance in most battles.<br><br>Starting as a high elf, my first 5 levels were spent leveling of bats/wolves/orcs in Gfaydark and as I hit lvl 8 I ventured into crushbone until 10.<br><br>From 11-12 i killed some mermaids in OOT, they were pretty easy (lvl 12 or so) but they always spawn/train in two's so a partner is good to have.<br><br>From 12-14 I leveled quickly killing dervs in No Ro with an experienced group.<br><br>Level 15-17 kept me in Oasis fighting those crocs, dry bones, and occasional ghouls.<br><br>Level 17 is where being a mage really kicked in as my lvl 16  Fire dd really started packing a punch with no fizzle problems.  I went to OOT and started killing gargoyles which are lvl 18-20 but can be leveled of easily until lvl 23.  Each gargoyle gave 1/3 a bulb of exp from 16-19 and then only the lvl 20's gave that.  These gargoyles were extremely easy to solo with an earth pet and my 16 Fire DD, and they dropped rare eyes which I sold for 8pp on sister isle.<br>Becareful, they do train and 4 specs are on top of the island.  Gargoyle eye needed for shovel of ponz quest.<br><br>Level 20-22 I moved to the goblin isle where headhunter goblins ranged from 20-23 and racked in even more exp solo and some with a group.  Also did some griffawns in NK.<br><br>Level 22-23 brought me to south karana where I gained easy levels of non KoS aviak rooks and darters.  Also centaurs were great exp.<br><br>Level 23-24 I got easy experiene soloing great skeletons in rathe mts which were lvl 22-27 with an earth pet.<br><br>Level 24-27 kept me bouncing from Aviak harriers to split paw gnolls in south karana, and back to rathe mts.  Also did some griffennes in NK.<br><br>Level 28-29 I spent in High Keep getting easy exp in a warrior or goblin raider group which go from lvl 30-34 usually and can level you to 35 at least.<br><br>Level 29-31 spent soloing aviak avocets which ranged from 29-32.  Not to hard to kill with earth pet and shock of spikes but get sow for safety and memorize the way to the lake rathe zone.<br><br>Level 31-34 back to high keep into warrior or raider group where I got my gloves of rallos zek for the earth pet research. (South Karana and North karana drop a lot of mage research items for lvl 16-29 so does OOT.)<br><br>Level 34-39 is when i got all my focus items from Temple of Ro and got my new 270 dd and 320 bolt or so.  Went to Frontier Mountains in Kunark to solo Mountain Giants and sometimes got into a group.  MG's are great experience upto level 43 in that zone since there are 4 different types of mg's ranging from lvl 32 to 37.  They drop rare loot (forest loop around 1kpp maybe less now, and a lot of 40-50pp weapons/tunics that can be sold to vendors.)  Also sarnak knights run around, brutes, burynais, and goblins.  All give great exp.<br><br>Level 39-41 I went to overthere and soloed for quick experience, (thorny succulents, tigresses, cockatrices, rhinos, sarnaks.)<br>Watch out for tigers, they are very mean and its a close battle when soloing them.  Tiger do give the best experience in that zone for level 39-41 since tigers are lvl 37-39.<br><br>Level 41-43 spent in frontier mts (near burning woods zone) soloing MG braes, craigs, Ravenous brutes, goblins, and burynai.  Burynai cenobytes are nasty, superior healing clerics which wont stop healing themselves when less than 1/2 hp.<br><br>Level 43-44 gained in overthere with ease.<br><br>Level 44-46 gained in oasis hunting specs and sg's.  Very fun, not too hard with an earth pet and the 580 dd shock of swords.  I make 200plat every few hours and those sg's are rich!!!<br><br><br>There are other plenty of places that I might not have mentioned or have not visited but these are the ones I liked and remember the most.<br><br>Some not mentioned are:<br><br>sol a (goblins)<br>The rest of karanas (griffs/named cyclops)<br>inside split paw (gnolls)<br>inside everfrost (hunting orcs and mammoths) inside perma<br>WC (hunting druids)<br>RV (hunting some guards)<br>kaladim (hunting dock dwarves)<br>OOT (hunting sea furies).<br><br>----------------------------------------------<br>Research info<br>----------------------------------------------<br>Most components are found of mobs 5 levels higher than the spell you're trying to research.<br><br>Level 16-29 words stuff can easily be found in OOT, NKar, SKar, High Keep.<br><br>Level 29-39 words and stuff can be found in higher level zones and dungeons like upper/lower Guk or Sol a/b.  Usually zones with lvl 30-40 mobs will have them.<br><br>Level 39-44 words components can be foudn in lvl 40+ zones like dreadlands and burningwoods in Kunark.  Skyfire and some dungeons also.  <br><br>49+ components are usually in the planes.<br><br>Level 50+ spells drop in a lot of kunark lvl 45+ zones.<br><br>Most lvl 16-39 components can be bought for 1-3pp each from vendors and other pc's using the /auction command.<br><br>-----------------------------------<br>Extra mage info<br>------------------------------------<br>A mage is a very balanced class; we can summon all the gear we need for battle and we usually enter battle with 6-7 bulbs of mana because of banked mana (summoned gear.)  A pet is 50% of your power, always have one out.<br><br>Soloing is the best way to get exp, but grouping doesnt hurt if hunting hard stuff.<br><br>Always give your pet sword of runes (those 40 procs that *still proc vs non summoned* that verant claimed to have patched help a lot).<br><br>Cold stones rock and so do dimensional holes/pockets to carry summoned gear or heavy stuff.<br><br>I carry 2 large sewing kits, 8 holes, can carry large items like scythes which bagpacks can't, and weight almost nothing.  I always right click to close/open them so I dont have the combine problem of losing everything inside them.<br><br>I also carry 2 large bags and I summon 2 dimensionals for very game.<br><br>Since a mages strength is very low you have to be able to compromise with your strength and carrying 3 weight bags is annoying.<br><br>I wear 4int/2str earrings and 7int/7str necklace to help with my str.  I dont bother getting 5 int earrings to lose the 2 str.  The 1 int tradoffs aren't worth the carrying ability.<br><br>Fire shield really helps lvl 34+ in the solo stage as your pet can last longer and vs more mobs.<br><br>Pets spells 39+, no longer need the heal summoned spell because they have regen.  And if your pet dies its a bad situation.<br><br>That resummon a new pet strat doesnt work too well.<br><br>Since mobs at lvl 39+ can kill your pet pretty fast and run fast, its pointless to try resummoning, its either you Win or you Run.<br><br>Get Jboots, they are a life saver.  Not as fast as sow, but faster than most mobs and easy to use.  Very easy to kite with jboots and the Win or Run strategy works great.<br><br>I carry usually 2-3 focus with me since I almost never use fire pet.<br><br>Earth pets rock solo wise or for root purposes<br>but hard to summon the highest lvl possible.<br><br>Water pets rock for kiting because easier to summon a higher lvl water pet that does more dmg and its ice DD rocks in taking down the hp of a running mob.  It also taunts pretty well if it gets a few hits off.<br><br>Air pets are easy to get high lvl with focus item,<br>fast agility, fast attacks, stun for caster type mobs, but not as usefull in most of my adventures.<br>In dungeons if they get lost, you will die anyways because no pet protection :)<br><br>Also The greatest trick for kiting, is run exactly through a mob and past your pet, its almost a gurantee that the pet will taunt the mob off you.  Try it twice and it should work with no doubt (strat borrowed from punkrop lvl 50+ mage on fennin ro).<br>------------------------------------------------<br>&nbsp;<br>Eendyar Soulseeker<br>46'th High Elf Mage <br>"Mythic Synergy"<br><a href="http://www.mythicsynergy.com" target=_new>http://www.mythicsynergy.com</a><br>Fennin Ro</td></tr>
