	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96672022711723><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96672022711723>Extra Pet Info.</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96672022711723#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Aug 19th 5:23 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>------------------------------------<br>Pet Commands / Hot key's<br>------------------------------------<br><br>There are 5 main commands that are very important to a magician.<br><br>/pet attack - makes pet attack mob<br>/pet follow me - makes the pet follow the mage<br>/pet guard here - makes the pet guard the spot<br>/pet back off - pet backs off a mob<br>/pet health report - reports pet's health<br>(/pet report health - also works).<br><br>(Also /pet taunt will turn the pet's taunt on/off.<br>Very usefull when grouped and you dont want the pet taking all the damage from a mob.)<br><br>I usually have my hotkey's set up to handle spells and pets.<br><br>1) Best DD<br>2) Backup DD<br>3) Malise type spell.<br>4) Fire shield spell<br>5) /pet follow me<br>6) /pet attack<br><br>The reason for the pet commands is I always type in manually when i want my pet to guard or when I want its hp report.&nbsp;&nbsp;I almost never use /pet back off at lvl 39+ because every mob triple hits and that makes it impossible to get that pet off.<br><br>If a mob hits your pet, that pet will keep fighting the mob. <br><br>The dd's are hotkeyed for quick access, fire shield for quick access, and malise for de-resist quick access.<br><br>------------------------------------<br>Pet Strategy and Use<br>------------------------------------<br><br>When soloing, it is always a good idea to make the pet guard and pull a mob to your pet.  However if that is not possible then the pet should always follow close behind.  Keep an eye on your pet so its not jumped or aggroed.<br><br>The perks of /pet guard here is the pet will stay there until something hits it or you issue another command.<br><br>-Whenever your pet kills something, it goes back to the guard spot.<br>-Whenever your pet is guarding, it heals faster.<br><br>I usually press f1 to toggle between me and pet.  First time its me, second time its pet and so on.<br>Before pulling I make sure pet has burnout (every 15 min) and then I fire shield it.<br>I pull a mob to my pet, and tell the pet to attack.<br><br>Most of the battle is hotkey/keyboard base.<br><br>------------------------------------<br>When to use what pet<br>------------------------------------<br><br>EARTH - Number one pet for soloing.  Great hp and the power to root your mob.  With a rooter you can unleash your dd fury without much fear of death.  A malise spell helps before nuking so that the pet's (procs/effects) stick to the mob effectively.  This is the only way mages get a root type spell so this pet is a must for every magicians book.  Low agility keeps this pet from lasting too long vs many mobs as it takes almost every hit and usually full dmg.  25-50% chance of summoning the highest level pet with focus item.<br><br>WATER - Well balanced pet.  Second in hp to earth but has higher ac and agility to my knowledge.  Its ice proc DD is powerfull and is cast pretty often.  I think it casts more often if the mage is hit.  Great pet to kite with if you have sow or jboots.  Nice dmg dealer in a group if you need good hp and good firepower. 50-75% chance of summoning the highest level pet with focus item.<br><br>AIR - Third on the hp chain, the air pet with its highest agility does the fastest attacks and evades the most hits.  With its ability to stun its a wonderful pet vs mobs that do a lot of attacks or especially caster mobs.  Its ability to self invis gives you a stealthy ability in dungeons, duels, and pvp.  50-60% chance of summoning the highest level pet with focus item.  This pet is not bad for kiting and will mow down enemies very fast in a group.<br><br>FIRE - The lowest hp pet with a self fire shield and a strong fire DD.  Doing twice the dmg of water's DD and its hella strong fireshield, usually the dmg of the pets level.  Very usefull to clear low trash or in a group that needs an ultra fast way to kill a mob.  It makes an average kite pet but should be used by a master because bad kiting can kill this pet fast.  50% chance of summoning the highest level pet with focus item or so.  Never used fire pets that much.<br>------------------------------------------------<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
