	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you are having a hard time with this aspect of a mage try switching pets. most of the time all the nuking will keep the MOB with an earth pet. you have to judge when you can nuke. usually with an air pet you have about 1-4 seconds depending on your level in which the mob will be stuned. and once you get high enough where you can afford it (30 or so) go to SK and buy all the gnoll hide lariats you can hold. you can buy them for 5-10p.<br>the low damage/delay doesn't effect the pet and they now can stun. these are best used with a water pet. <br><br>Damage shields also help keep a mob off you. you see the way a mob decides who to go after is "who is hurting me the most?". if you pull with a 300 point spell you have to realize that unless you have an earth pet you will be the primary target for quite awhile. my advice is to malise pull, sic pet, then nuke,wait 2 or 3 rounds,nuke again,<br>let pet hit the mob and let the damage shield do its thing, recast pet if needbe, repeat. <br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Speel Lavamaster<br>magician , monk , and warrior extrodinaire.<br></td></tr>
