	   <tr><td colspan=2>Water pets are definately the one pet to buy through all the levels if you are very low on money and can only buy just that one. I wouldn't say they are the 'top' pets in the game though. Other pets are better in different places(other magician pets that is, water pets are supreme to any non-magician pet).<br><br>Now, even though just buying a water pet will save you money at lower levels, it sucks to chain-research them at higher levels. It is very costly. Think of this: to get your level 49 water pet you have to buy the level 34 water pet and use it to research the 39 water pet. Then you have to use the 39 water pet to research the 44 water pet. THEN you have to use the 44 water pet to resarch the level 49 water pet.<br><br>Since you won't suceed in researching every time you will end up having to buy the level 34 water pet about 5 times. Plus you have to track down all the words/extra component for all these pets, often buying them. In the end you have spent a lot of time and money. Its the same thing(only not as bad) if you wan't your level 29 water pet. Water pets can only be bought at level 34 - post 20(which sucks).<br><br>Corpusnuntia/Divineshadow/Naltec/Natalos/Sunsong/Plantmaster/Zuranthium<br><br>Player of many characters ont he Nameless server.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
