	   <a name=96660398419802></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f96660398419802><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96660398419802>Bacan</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=96660398419802#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Aug 18th 9:06 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.38]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Soloing guide for your HElf Mage (lvls 1-28)<br> Im here to post my sistem for leveling newbye caracters starting around Faydwer. This system has been proved with a Mage, Wizzy, Druid, Cleric Warrior, and finally a Pally =P. This guide is oriented to Mages, if your another class you may need to group or solo the targets a lvl or two later.<br> First thing to do, go to your guild and deliver your newbie note, mem your first spells and go out to GFay, start hunting by your newbie zone. I usually use the place to the right of the entrance to Felwithe, its delimited by the road to Keletin and 3 hills. Very few orcs roam this place so its a great place for Lvls1-3 (you'll get killed by them almost always at this levels, so dont attack them).<br> Get to that place and start killing the bats, wasp, skellys, and if your bold the wolves. Do this and you'll get to Lvl 3 in no time ( be sure to keep all the bone chips and bat wings for selling or questing).<br> At level 3 you finally can do the Pawns with no fear so kill all of them on sight (keep the hatchets for the quest in the rangers guild).<br> At lvl 4 you get your new spells so go to the guild and buy your pet and your DD spells first. Buy some malachite and go to Butcherblock Mts (BB). Here start doing the snakes that are yellow or even con to you. You'll kick some serious a%$# here with your powerful pet and new spells, althought be sure to tank for your pet a little cause hes not to strong yet (i recommend using Water till lvl 25 or so if you are soloing).<br> At lvl 5 or 6 start doing the Bats, Goblins and Dwarf skellys that room near the 2 huts and you'll get to 7 in no time.<br> When you hit 7, go to Druid ring in BB and start camping the skellys that spawn there (its a 5 spawn camp, the last one is behind a hill). You'll stay here till lvl 9 so be sure to take a little trip to Fel to buy your rank 3 spells.<br> When you hit 9 go to LFay and do the Nybright systers, you ned a group for this till vl 12 or so, but at 12 you can start pulling only 2 and killing them solo. You'll get to 15 doing this in no time. And then is the boring Croc time in Oasis of Marr.<br> Kill the Croc acording to your level solo till lvl 18 or 19 (to level real fast kill only yellow cons).<br> So now comes the easy camping time. Everybody is busy killing the Aviaks at Rathe or SKarana, but your a Mage, and you kick butt solo, so go to EKarana and start doing Gnoll Reavers and wolves there solo, you can get great exp doing this and some nice loot too.<br> When Gnolls and wolves start to get too low level for you, you can start soloing the white or yellow con Crag spiders (be sure to use water pet), i guess that us Mages and Druids are the only ppl soloing them so you'll get plenty of targets. Camp yourself near the Barbarian Village and hunt at the mountain range (be sure to keep an eye on any HG that pops around). You'll get to Lvl 28 doing this in almost no time.<br> And here is when my Hunting guide ends, the following guide will take you till lvl 50.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
