	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey Speel i agree with you on a few points however I DON'T like the pet re-cast strategy. Here is why: first of all since you will be casting nothing but pets and damage shields you won't outdamage your pet, and thefore only get half of the exp. for the kill. Secondly, it takes a while to down a monster using this strategy, so in the time you killed that cyclop's getting half of the exp. for the kill, you could have killed 2 cylops's, getting full exp. for each kill, so in reality BETTER EXP. <br><br>Thats also why I think necros are better soloer's than magicians. Even though they sometimes can't take things that are as big, becuase of massive spell resists, they can take many small things with almost no downtime, and make exp. faster than the magician who is using the chain-pet strategy. Plus, if things get hairy the magician has one unreliable escape route - gate. Necros have shadow step, gate, brief invulnerbilty, feign death, the darkness line, root, fear, screaming terror(a MEZMERIZE SPELL GOTTEN AT LEVEL 24).<br><br>I love magicians, but I don't like the pet-recast strategy and just becuase 'magicians can take bigger monsters than any other class' that doesn't mean it is better. Bigger isn't always better you know. Just my 2cp that I know are correct, accurate, and a good tip. =:-)<br><br>Corpusnuntia, Divineshadow, Natalos, Naltec, Plantmaster, Zuranthium<br><br>Player of many characters on the Nameless server.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
