	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.33]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Nothing wrong with healing into the mid 20's to upper 20's.&nbsp;&nbsp;The key is to do it the right way.  You want to heal on a water pet. It's regen is good and its better than average agility means that it doesn't get hit every time a mob swings.  Heal when your pet is superior, so high blue pet on a low blue or green mob.  In this situation your pet takes many fewer hits so the heal will give a lot of extra rounds.  In earlier levels when you can still cast yellow and black pets this strategy works great.  Turn your pet loose sit and med.  Heal once and med.  Then you go right to the next mob.  The downside is that the pet will take more exp, so it makes sense to do this in an enviroment where there is a steady stream of Mobs.  I leveled very quickly from 12 to 24 using this when it made sense.  Earth pet and nuking is also a good way to go when you have mobs that are better than your pet or there is a thin flow of the mobs so you have lots of time to heal.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
