	   <tr><td colspan=2>Mage of the 42nd circle.<br><br>Hail Fellows, I have travelled many leagues over this plane of earth called Norrath and have battled many wonderous creatures in obtaining the status in which I write to you this day. As a youth within my earlier levels..say 5-14 I hunted a lot in lavastorm. Good quiet hunting for a Young Tier Dal. but as I grew I began my trekking into the North and South regions of the Deserts of RO. These offered many good Dervish cuttthroat camps, They are always good for slaying, and many other things of interests. Giant Spiders, Puma's and Madmen. Also I hit a very secluded and great hunting area many do not fear to tread. Rathe Mountains. I along with a friend, an Enchanter did very very well there hunting the Orc and Lizardmen camps throughout the zone. they seems to be far enough away from any giants streching thier huge legs, so we had a field day. Now I did this from 14 - 17, after 17 I hit the Skeleton camp in the rathe mounts, excellent expeirince and the undead are always good for a chuckle or 2 :), Now after twenty I found spells to be quite expensive and I began my Mage Quests from the temple of RO, these quests give excellent xp right about 20-24 so do them then and watch the bar turn orange alot. I also&nbsp;&nbsp;began hunting in OOT at the Undead Isle. great mony and XP on the Gargs, but watch what time you go. Try the Off peak hours, as during primetime it is packed and everyone kills all the gargs they can find, thus depleting the loot of eye's which sell for quite a bit. If OOT is too packed to hunt, forget it and Hit the Gnolls in Lake rathe great faction hits in Qyenos and good items, xp isnt too bad either on the late night skels. Now after 24 I was due for an Ocean voyage and Mistmoore was my newest vacation spot. AWESOME XP around the entrance pond. just stay away from the zone line unless you can handle the constant trains as they come furious and often. Now After about 24 - 32 I had hit Mistmoore and my old haunt Rathe mounts for cyclops.<br>from 34 - on up it was Kunark and overthere, Sarnaks hate the smell of me coming from the boat now. hehe this is a basic idea of where you can get good hunting experience away from the bustling crowds. Hunt well friends and remember Mages and Pets are worth theyre weight in gold. but a follish mage is Death waiting to happen. until then Keep hunting.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
