	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok..a brief synopsis of what I have done to get to L36.&nbsp;&nbsp;Gnome Magician btw.<br><br>1 to 12...steamfont (the loot is awful, leave asap)<br><br>13 to 14  North Ro killing giant snakes for fangs because I was super broke from being in Steamfont.  I basically killed whatever was blue to me and I could solo in North Ro and area.<br><br>15 to 20   OASIS Crocs and Orcs. Orcs are great and u get some half decent loot.  The crocs I did solo and orcs I grouped.<br><br>20 to 24  LAKE RATHE. Aviak guards are amazing xp.  I grouped and solo'd.<br><br>24 to 35  HIGH KEEP.  This place is totally amazing.  Good loot and xp.  Bank right beside u.  Just make sure you don't mind being in a small room for a long long time.  Waiting to get into a group can be a pain...but hey, do what I did..become a master brewer while u wait..hehe. I grouped here too.  Also, if u wanted you can get to Level 40 here, but gawd...who would want to?<br><br>35 to 36 Sol B. Kill Kobolds.  This place is great xp and good loot.  You can stay here to at least 45-48. Not sure, my highest character is L40.  I mostly grouped...heh, I solo'd a few on occasion under the right conditions.  Waiting for a group can be a major pain.  I am considering leaving for a Kunark zone to do something new.  Maybe Dreadlands, Overthere or Frontier Mountains.  Lower Guk is also an option, but LG is better for getting GREAT loot...while SolB is better xp and basic loot (coinage etc..).  The diff between SolB and LG is probably not all that great, so whatever suits your fancy.<br><br>I did all this an 15 days played time.  Not to mention I am a master brewer, master smith and master baker.  I think that's not too bad...not the best, but definately not the worst =).<br><br>Cheers, <br><br>Beep.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
