	   <tr><td colspan=2>Something i need to add about pets,<br><br>The earth pet:Has low agi about 70 gets hit far to offend,very high hp low ac and hits just as hard as a water elemental but with the str/sta of an ogre and the ability to cast root(note:earth pets are resistant to magic increasing 1 point per lvl of the pet).<br><br>The water elemental:has high agi about 115 the str/sta of a troll,about 50 less hp thene a earth elmental but very high ac and does a 25 dmg nuke at lvl 12,can hit for a max of 45 dmg a round(an earth pet can hit for about 35 because it doesnt have the nuke)is immune to ALL poisons.<br>(the dmg i said could be dealt is only if the pet has a 10 dmg weapon, dly doesnt matter,and if it double attacks bashes and casts in the same round,this doesnt happen much at lower lvls).<br><br>The air elemental:<br>can cast invis on itself,can cast a druid spell called whirlwind wich does about 15 dmg and may stun,has an incredibly high agi of about 140!!!! has fairy low ac and hp (doesnt get hit alot but if something casts on it, watch out).<br><br>The fire elemental:<br>can cast a dmg shield on itself,hits very hard and fast with about the base stats of a human shadow knight,awfully low hp,i think 100 less thene a water elemental of the same lvl and much less ac thene an air elemental.<br><br>So what pet do you want tanking for you?:<br>Well i suggest air or water,earth may seem like a good choice for soloing but i used earth with my other mage and im using water with my current mage ,water is much better in my oppinion,if your fighting mobs that hit fast but not hard use air, if your fighting mobs that hit hard but miss alot use water,if your fighting mobs that hit and miss with average dmg/dly use earth,if your fighting mobs that hit alot but not hard use fire.<br><br>Note:everything im saying about hp\ac and dmg\dly ratios is based upon pets from lvl 8-20.<br><br>Have fun,<br>Naeluuven 15th mage of the Xegony server<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
